Enum DatatypeValidation

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<DatatypeValidation>
      com.fluidops.iwb.api.editor.DatatypeValidation
All Implemented Interfaces:
Validation, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DatatypeValidation>
public enum DatatypeValidation
extends java.lang.Enum<DatatypeValidation>
implements Validation

This class provides standard validators for known types, e.g. the most important XML schema types as defined in http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/ This enumeration can be used for type based evaluation, i.e. if the target type of some output is known. The enumeration provides a convenience method to retrieve a fitting validator, c.f. validatorFor(URI). If a validator is available it is returned and the validate(String) method can be used. Otherwise, null is returned. In the Information Workbench we support Datatypes as defined in Datatype. For each of these we have a matching validator.

Author:
as
